thread.title: Fed Sets May 30 Vote on Proposed Volcker Rule Changes

author: Ryan Tracy
title: Fed Sets May 30 Vote on Proposed Volcker Rule Changes
text:
The Federal Reserve set a May 30 vote on proposed changes to the Volcker rule, the first public step in an expected rewrite of the restrictions that have held back bank trading desks for years.
The rule, part of the 2010 Dodd-Frank financial law, bans traders at taxpayer-insured banks from speculating but allows them to buy and sell securities in concert with customersâ€™ demand.
